descript.abstract: This line data layer represents bus routes for the City of Madison, Wisconsin in 2014. It is a feature class within the geodatabase, Madison_City_BusRoutes_2014.gdb. Other feature classes in this geodatabase include: Bus_Stops, ParkRide, Route_Pattern, Route_Trips, Suburban_Transit_Routes and Suburban_Transit_Stops. [Bus Routes (simplified to one feature per route number). Metro Transit, March 2, 2014. GTFS v.62 feed_start_date 20140302 feed_end_date 20140524 feed_version 201403031051 https://developers.google.com/transit/gtfs/reference#General_Transit_Feedfeed_start_date 20130825 http://www.cityofmadison.com/metro/Apps/developers.cfm]
descript.purpose: This layer is intended for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production, or to provide a basemap to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. [Display mapping, analysis.]
descript.supplinf: Augmented original metadata with UW-Madison specific elements. For additional information, please see original license/data sharing agreement where applicable. The data for this layer was published with multiple feature classes, and the metadata was generated from the "Madison_City_BusRoutes_2014" layer.
